RELEASE NOTE
INTRODUCTION:
This release introduces improvements in Refund Service and Operation Service. It mainly focuses on refund processing, reconciliation improvements, SFTP handling, and system stability enhancements.
OVERVIEW:
This release focuses on enhancing refund reliability and operational processing. It includes fixes for refund failure scenarios, improvements in reconciliation for multi-account transactions, file handling enhancements, and system upgrades including Spring Boot version update and security fixes.
CODE CHANGES / CONFIG / DB CHANGES:
Refund Service (v1.2.0)
Implemented refund failure handling improvements
Fixed issues in refund failed scenarios
Modified booked refund UPI query for better performance
Added new status "refundProcess" when SFTP fails
Operation Service (v1.4.0)
Improved reconciliation process for multi-account transactions
Updated settlement status to COMPLETED
Fixed data synchronization issues
Upgraded Spring Boot from 3.3.10 to 3.5.9 and fixed vulnerabilities
Handled "null" string values in multi-account parsing
Added file path validation
Uploaded recon bad records file to RECON/OUT folder
Added SFTP OUT path configuration
Implemented checksum validation for file integrity
Added DB synonyms and grants for APPADMIN
Enabled actuator health, liveness, and readiness checks
Ignored negative amount while parsing recon file
Fixed incorrect bank reference number issue in production
PREVIOUS IMPACT:
Refund failures were not handled properly
Issues in UPI refund query performance
Missing status handling when SFTP fails
Reconciliation issues in multi-account transactions
Data sync inconsistencies
File handling and validation gaps
Incorrect bank reference number in production
Negative amounts causing parsing issues
IMPACT OF CHANGES:
Improved refund processing and failure handling
Better tracking of SFTP failures using new status
Accurate and optimized UPI refund processing
Improved reconciliation accuracy
Stable data synchronization across services
Better file handling and validation
Improved system monitoring with actuator
Increased security with dependency upgrades
Correct bank reference handling
Cleaner recon processing by ignoring invalid data
ROLLBACK PLAN:
Revert service code changes to previous version
Restore previous configurations and behavior
Disable new features related to reconciliation and SFTP handling if required
